#: ../../../discord.rst:6
msgid "Creating a Bot Account"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../discord.rst:8
msgid ""
"In order to work with the library and the Discord API in general, we must "
"first create a Discord Bot account."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../discord.rst:10
msgid "Creating a Bot account is a pretty straightforward process."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../discord.rst:12 ../../../discord.rst:61
msgid ""
"Make sure you're logged on to the `Discord website <https://discord.com>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../discord.rst:13 ../../../discord.rst:62
msgid ""
"Navigate to the `application page <https://discord.com/developers/"
"applications>`_"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../discord.rst:14
msgid "Click on the \"New Application\" button."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../discord.rst:0
msgid "The new application button."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../discord.rst:19
msgid "Give the application a name and click \"Create\"."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../discord.rst:0
msgid "The new application form filled in."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../discord.rst:24
msgid "Navigate to the \"Bot\" tab to configure it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../discord.rst:25
msgid ""
"Make sure that **Public Bot** is ticked if you want others to invite your "
"bot."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../discord.rst:27
msgid ""
"You should also make sure that **Require OAuth2 Code Grant** is unchecked "
"unless you are developing a service that needs it. If you're unsure, then "
"**leave it unchecked**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../discord.rst:0
msgid "How the Bot User options should look like for most people."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../discord.rst:33
msgid "Copy the token using the \"Copy\" button."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../discord.rst:35
msgid "**This is not the Client Secret at the General Information page.**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../discord.rst:39
msgid ""
"It should be worth noting that this token is essentially your bot's "
"password. You should **never** share this with someone else. In doing so, "
"someone can log in to your bot and do malicious things, such as leaving "
"servers, ban all members inside a server, or pinging everyone maliciously."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../discord.rst:44
msgid "The possibilities are endless, so **do not share this token.**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../discord.rst:46
msgid ""
"If you accidentally leaked your token, click the \"Regenerate\" button as "
"soon as possible. This revokes your old token and re-generates a new one. "
"Now you need to use the new token to login."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../discord.rst:50
msgid ""
"And that's it. You now have a bot account and you can login with that token."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../discord.rst:55
msgid "Inviting Your Bot"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../discord.rst:57
msgid "So you've made a Bot User but it's not actually in any server."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../discord.rst:59
msgid "If you want to invite your bot you must create an invite URL for it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../discord.rst:63
msgid "Click on your bot's page."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../discord.rst:64
msgid "Go to the \"OAuth2 > URL Generator\" tab."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../discord.rst:0
msgid "How the OAuth2 page should look like."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../discord.rst:69
msgid "Tick the \"bot\" checkbox under \"scopes\"."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../discord.rst:0
msgid "The scopes checkbox with \"bot\" ticked."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../discord.rst:74
msgid ""
"Tick the permissions required for your bot to function under \"Bot "
"Permissions\"."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../discord.rst:76
msgid ""
"Please be aware of the consequences of requiring your bot to have the "
"\"Administrator\" permission."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../discord.rst:78
msgid ""
"Bot owners must have 2FA enabled for certain actions and permissions when "
"added in servers that have Server-Wide 2FA enabled. Check the `2FA support "
"page <https://support.discord.com/hc/en-us/articles/219576828-Setting-up-Two-"
"Factor-Authentication>`_ for more information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../discord.rst:0
msgid "The permission checkboxes with some permissions checked."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../discord.rst:83
msgid ""
"Now the resulting URL can be used to add your bot to a server. Copy and "
"paste the URL into your browser, choose a server to invite the bot to, and "
"click \"Authorize\"."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../discord.rst:88
msgid "The person adding the bot needs \"Manage Server\" permissions to do so."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../discord.rst:90
msgid ""
"If you want to generate this URL dynamically at run-time inside your bot and "
"using the :class:`discord.Permissions` interface, you can use :func:`discord."
"utils.oauth_url`."
msgstr ""
